properties.areaDesc: Indian Wells Valley; Kern County Desert; Tehachapi Area
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 15 at 8:35PM PST until January 17 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Sustained southwest to west winds 20 to 30 mph, with
gusts near 55 mph expected.

* WHERE...Tehachapi Area, Indian Wells Valley, and Kern County
Desert, including the towns of Mojave and Inyokern.

* WHEN...Valid from 4 PM PST Thursday afternoon until 7 AM PST
Friday morning.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Strong wind gusts may blow down tree limbs and power lines. A
few power outages are possible. Travel will be difficult,
particularly for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways affected include, but are not
limited to Highway 14, U.S. Highway 395, Highway 58 below
Tehachapi Pass, including the town of Mojave, and Highway 178
below Walker Pass, including the town of Inyokern.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THURSDAY TO 7 AM PST FRIDAY
